cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on the analysis of scientists on Twitter, which involves social media and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the demographics and interconnectivity of scientists, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The analysis of shared URLs could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
